# Template for GitHub repo secrets.
#
# Copy this file to .env (which is gitignored) and fill in the real values
# as you work through Tasks 1, 3, 4, 11, 12 of the migration plan.
#
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# When every line is filled, tell Claude "env is ready" and Claude will push
# these into GitHub repo secrets via `gh secret set` (Task 9).
#
# DELETE .env after the secrets are uploaded. These values belong in:
#   1. Your password manager (authoritative copy)
#   2. GitHub repo secrets (where the workflow reads them)
# Nowhere else — especially not on disk.

# ----- Task 1: NVD API key -----
# Request at https://nvd.nist.gov/developers/request-an-api-key
# Use your personal email, not Cisco.
NVD_API_KEY=

# ----- Task 3: Cloudflare R2 -----
# From the Cloudflare dashboard -> R2 -> Overview (right sidebar) for account ID,
# then R2 -> Manage R2 API Tokens -> Create API Token for the access key / secret.
# Scope: Object Read & Write on bucket "nvd-handsonhacking". TTL: no expiration.
R2_ACCOUNT_ID=
R2_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
R2_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
R2_BUCKET=nvd-handsonhacking

# ----- Task 12: Cloudflare zone-scoped API token (cache purge) -----
# Created AFTER the domain is on Cloudflare (Task 11).
# Zone ID: Cloudflare dashboard -> handsonhacking.org -> Overview -> right sidebar.
# API token: My Profile -> API Tokens -> Create Token -> "Edit zone DNS" template,
#   then customize: permission = Zone -> Cache Purge -> Purge, specific zone only.
# Leave these blank for now — we'll fill them in during Task 12.
CLOUDFLARE_ZONE_ID=
CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=

# ----- Task 4: healthchecks.io ping URL -----
# https://healthchecks.io -> New Check.
# Name: nvd-scrapper, Period: 3h, Grace: 12h. Copy the ping URL (https://hc-ping.com/...).
HEALTHCHECKS_PING_URL=
